Project: Multi-Agent Financial Analysis System
Course: Big Data Analysis
Student: ALEKSEEVA ANNA 1820259022

This system automates stock analysis using specialized AI agents that work together like a financial team

Architecture:
src/
├── agents
│   ├── analysis_agent.py
│   ├── base_agent.py
│   ├── data_agent.py
│   └── report_agent.py
├── chains
│   ├── data_analysis_chain.py
│   └── technical_analysis_chain.py
├── dashboard
│   └── app.py
├── llm
│   └── llm_factory.py
├── mcp_servers
│   └── financial_data_server.py
├── memory
│   └── short_term_memory.py
├── monitoring
│   └── health_monitor.py
├── optimization

Each agent has a specific role. The Manager Agent coordinates them all, similar to how a project manager works



PART 1

Step 1: Check System Status
Let's check if all components are working. We can see Ollama is available, and all agents are ready
-- python scripts/start_system.py status

Step 2: System Test
Now testing all system components. All tests pass successfully
-- python scripts/start_system.py test

Step 3: Demo Mode
Let's demo with multiple stocks. The system analyzes AAPL, MSFT, and GOOGL, giving different recommendations for each
-- python scripts/start_system.py demo

Step 4: Full Analysis
-- python scripts/start_system.py analyze --ticker AAPL --timeframe 1mo

Step 5: Show Results
The system creates detailed JSON reports. Each report includes executive summary, technical analysis, sentiment scores, risk assessment, and AI insights.
-- ls -la reports/
-- ls -la results/



PART 2

Feature 1: Real AI Insights
The LLM Agent provides human-like analysis, explaining market conditions and investment rationale
-- grep -A 10 "llm_insights" reports/AAPL_report_*.json

Feature 2: Risk Assessment
Automatic risk scoring helps investors understand potential downsides
-- grep -A 5 "risk_assessment" reports/AAPL_report_*.json

Feature 3: Quick Analysis
For rapid decisions, there's a quick mode that provides recommendations without LLM
-- python scripts/start_system.py quick --ticker TSLA


PART 3

Technical Details
Framework: LangChain + CrewAI
LLM: Ollama (Mistral, Llama3.1)
Data: Yahoo Finance API
Output: JSON reports
CLI: Rich library for beautiful interface


This project demonstrates how multi-agent AI systems can automate complex financial workflows. The architecture is extensible for adding more data sources and analysis types

